  "prompt": "What is kale called in Hindi or Marathi?",
  "response": "In Hindi, kale is commonly referred to as \"\u0915\u093e\u0932\u0947 \u091a\u0928\u094b\u0902\" or \"\u0915\u093e\u0932\u0940 \u0917\u094b\u092d\u0940\" depending on the variety, although \"\u0915ale\" as a specific term might not have a direct translation since it is not a traditional Indian vegetable. In Marathi, it is referred to as \"\u0915\u093e\u0932\u0947 \u092a\u093e\u0928\" or simply \"\u0915\u093e\u0932\u0947\". However, it's worth noting that kale is not as commonly used in Indian cuisine as other leafy greens, so it might be referred to as 'kale' in many places.",
